    <h1>Repair USB B Female Port AKAI EIE</h1>

    <p>This is a repair log for repairing the USB type B female port located on the back of the interface.</p>

    <h2>Rationale</h2>
    <p>
        With the difficulty of a job like this on a crucial piece of equipment for my setup, I normally would not do this. But I have no other option and need
        this interface in 16 days from this date. I would really strongly prefer not to purchase something else, so I bought USB type B female USB connectors
        from Amazon. Here's the one I bought:
    </p>

    <img src={akai_eie_0.src} alt="AKAI EIE front view" />

    <p>
        <a href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B07F9KWHQG/ref=ppx_yo_dt_b_asin_title_o00_s00?ie=UTF8&psc=1"> USB Type B Female Port </a>
    </p>

